Multiplexing RTP Data and Control
Packets on a Single Port
2010", shape=ellipse, URL="RFC5761.html", target="_top", tooltip="This memo discusses issues that arise when multiplexing RTP data packets and RTP Control Protocol (RTCP) packets on a single UDP port.  It updates RFC 3550 and RFC 3551 to describe when such multiplexing is and is not appropriate, and it explains how the Session Description Protocol (SDP) can be used to signal multiplexed sessions. [STANDARDS-TRACK]"];
